INSERT INTO `plays` VALUES (9,'https://www.youtube.com/embed/NK_e5_fKtIo',1,14,1,'<p>Good song and good dancing</p>','2016-08-24 10:33:22','2016-08-24 10:33:22','Wicked','https://www.youtube.com/embed/NK_e5_fKtIo',37,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(10,'https://www.youtube.com/embed/ZYeVF9m9wdo',NULL,14,1,'<p>When you really look at it, life is plain simple. We always act as if something was promised to us but it really is not! Everything that we are given is extra. The present as they say is a gift; it is an unexpected thing that lands in our hands, we do not deserve it any better than&nbsp;any other being.</p>\r\n<p>The mind seems to have loads of barriers which really are not ones. Limits, like fears, are just an illusion, said Michael Jordan. Now that is something to take away from someone that has been tried over and over again, still stood up and raised high. I even think that MJ had more mental strength than talent. He was an elite basketball player, that is for sure, but how many other guys can claim the same if not more talent. Thing is when you play at such a high level, pressure kicks in and if you cannot handle this, your talent alone will not make you shine without some mental strength. You can tell MJ was having fun playing basketball; he would not take easy lay ups, he would often do the show with crazy wicked moves. Now that is a sign of someone having fun; it is almost as if his mind would say: &ldquo;It is too easy, I am not being challenged enough here; let me level up the the difficulty level and have some fun!&ldquo;. It seemed as if he had not much of mental barriers, as if he played like he had nothing to lose, as if he was always saying &ldquo;Why not?&rdquo;. MJ dunked and had his god damn tongue out all the time; why your tongue out MJ? Maybe because he just wanted, he was used to it that way!? and in the end why not? He was a character. <br />There seems to be within us some sort of battle of the egos;&nbsp;there is often one struggling but sticking to society lines while conflicting with its true nature and its call in life.</p>\r\n<p>So why struggle with barriers which in reality are not ones? I, personally, have made the decision that whenever I feel like fear is the one factor holding me back, I would go ahead and do it just for the sake of kicking fear&rsquo;s ass. Really, there is so much that could go wrong, so much out of one&rsquo;s control that everyone owes themselves some courage and do what they want for nothing is guaranteed; both good and bad are always possible outcomes so do yourself a favor and believe in the better! Somebody said it best with&nbsp;&ldquo;Courage is not the absence of fear, but the judgement that something is more important than that fear&rdquo;. You cannot let fear control your decisions, as living in fear is not living at all.</p>','2017-02-16 11:03:03','2017-02-16 11:03:03','Once in a while I ask myself, what am I doing?','https://www.youtube.com/embed/ZYeVF9m9wdo',59,1,NULL,NULL,4),(11,'https://www.youtube.com/embed/4sSKWNV3Gvk',1,14,1,'<p>Ever thought why something you find great is so underrated? Don\'t they see? That is how I feel about this song; for me it is one of the best songs ever made, period! I remember, when it came out, we used to go mad happy when it was played in the club, singing along the lyrics and asking the DJ for a replay. But for some reason it never really kikced in with the mainstream people! Timbaland was on fire at that moment and all eyes were on him, so why didn\'t this become a classic? Plus we love Jojo, don\'t we!?</p>','2016-09-02 12:00:54','2016-09-02 12:00:54','Talkin\' about my bae','https://www.youtube.com/embed/4sSKWNV3Gvk',47,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(12,'https://www.youtube.com/embed/BPwCd9vjO6E',1,14,1,'<p>Drake\'s music is sometimes best when you are down. I was listening to <strong>Nothing was the same</strong> album and thinking: When Rihanna dumps your ass, we\'re gonna have such a great album Drake! I don\'t wish it for you though, I love your music!</p>','2016-09-02 12:05:34','2016-09-02 12:05:34','Don\'t think about it too much','https://www.youtube.com/embed/BPwCd9vjO6E',48,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(13,'https://www.youtube.com/embed/eqceBawW4kM',1,14,1,'<p>Still a hall famer song; it&rsquo;s very catchy, kinda wanna take you into doing a little two steps dance move. It is a cute song, nothing very outstanding but I find it so good! Definitely one of my favorites. Jaicko says he likes nice things but does not need them to be happy, kinda capture the spirit of a humble baller: yes flash it once in a while if you can but don&rsquo;t let it get to your head, you know what I mean?! Live big or live broke, you can still be happy.</p>','2016-09-04 21:54:46','2016-09-04 21:54:46','Two Piece','https://www.youtube.com/embed/eqceBawW4kM',49,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(14,'https://www.youtube.com/embed/5nmdwd4ZTRI',1,14,1,'<p>What a catchy and nice ad. Some days, I just cannot get the melody out of my mind, especially when I am in a good mood; I wished I walked the strrets screaming to the world to be free and to be tropcial while doing the Carlton dance like the mangoe :-).</p>\r\n<p>I find the concept to be absolutely creative, enternaining and fun. First and for most, I love the music but there is so much more that makes the ad special. The allusion to the colorful vibe from the tropics coupled with the play around the word \"free\" (which, in the ad, is \"fruit\") makes this brilliant ad ideal for selling a tropical drink. The fruits dancing and listenning to music only make if more awesome!</p>','2016-11-01 21:58:44','2017-01-16 14:23:43','Be Fruit, Be Tropical','https://www.youtube.com/embed/5nmdwd4ZTRI',58,0,NULL,NULL,10),(15,'https://www.youtube.com/embed/k8Gsn4hWRNA',1,14,1,'<p>Russel Westbrook is one exceptional fella;&nbsp;he plays very well and has been described as the natural successor to Kobe Bryant and Michael Jordan: he\' s got the killer instinct as they say. But what marks me the most about Russ is the way he handles himself; he does not seem to care much about other people\'s opinions of him. Not only can you tell by the way he plays but also by the way he acts in public; he starts of the games by a choreography with a teammate, he dresses in controversial ways and he barely ever publicly speak when he is not serving his duties.<br />To do what one want is an ad made&nbsp;for him; he does what pleases him and despite him not always having the right call (in my opinion), I would still pick someone who take the risk to do something for themselves over someone&nbsp;who sit and criticize other people\'s actions from their&nbsp;couch, without ever putting themselves out there to experience how hard it actually is to step out of one\'s comfort.</p>\r\n<p>To kick the year well off,&nbsp;let\'s do like Russ&nbsp;and do what we the heck we want!</p>','2017-01-08 19:03:12','2017-01-14 15:12:06','Now I do what I want in 2017','https://www.youtube.com/embed/k8Gsn4hWRNA',60,0,NULL,NULL,10),(16,'https://www.youtube.com/embed/kXcwxLU7lHM',1,14,1,'<p>I&nbsp;like the fact that underground music is becoming more accessible to the general public; put your track on Youtube, let a vlogger use it in a video and there lies a good music discovery for a set of people who would never have found a song, if not broadcasted&nbsp;by the mainstream radio.<br />Props to all these DJs remixing random tracks and making them also&nbsp;enjoyable to a different&nbsp;public, i like where all this is going. I would have not listened to the original song until the end but this remix is just off the hook. The marching-band-like instruments rock the whole song and add a festive and dancehall side to it that only makes the track sehr&nbsp;good!!</p>','2017-01-08 19:22:38','2017-02-10 16:56:04','Oh you will become true','https://www.youtube.com/embed/kXcwxLU7lHM',61,0,NULL,NULL,14),(18,'https://www.youtube.com/embed/9UCY_U4QwqI',1,14,1,'<p>Classic!</p>','2017-01-09 13:22:23','2017-01-09 13:22:23','Where the 